						<summary>

						<p>This is much damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1373, • • • Śrāvaṇa, ba. 10, Ādivāra,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1451 August 21, Saturday</hi> (not Sunday), in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Mallikārjunadēva.</hi> It records that, when the <hi rend="italic">Mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Vallabhadēva-Daṇāyaka</hi> was ruling the <hi rend="bold">Bārakūra-rājya,</hi> a gift of 48 <hi rend="italic">honnus,</hi> which was the income from salt pans in <hi rend="bold">Kundāpura,</hi> was made to Jōyisa <hi rend="bold">Hariyappa</hi> of Maudgalya-<hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> and Ṛik-<hi rend="italic">śākhā.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
